item.description:
Methods In Java, when you declare class methods, you need to declare them inside the class:
public class Plane { public void fly() { System.out.println(&quot;I'm flying&quot;); } }  In Kotlin, you can declare in two different ways:
class Plane() { fun fly() { println(&quot;I'm flying&quot;) } } // or class Plane fun Plane.fly() { println(&quot;I'm flying&quot;) } // or class Plane fun Plane.fly() = println(&quot;I'm flying&quot;)  It&rsquo;s interesting to note that other languages (like Golang) also uses the second form.
